      <div type="apparatus">
        <head>Apparatus</head>
        <p>The monument appears to be complete below; it must be assumed that it originally stood on another feature on which the last line of the epigram was inscribed.</p>
        <p>l. 9, <foreign lang="grc">ΤΕΙΡΕΕΙ</foreign>, corrected by Cormack and Robert.</p>
      </div>

      <div type="translation">
        <head>Translation</head>
        <ab>He did not die, nor did he see the stream of Acheron, but in Olympus Asklepiodotos is among the stars—he who also built many splendid things for his motherland <gap dim="bottom" extent="1" unit="line" reason="lost"/></ab>
      </div>

      <div type="commentary">
        <head>Commentary</head>
        <p>See  <xref type="inscription" n="53" href="110068">11.68</xref>, and discussion at <xref type="eAla-text" n="V.8">V.8</xref>.</p>
      </div>

